Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: SQLAlchemy-UTCDateTime
Version: 1.0.4
Summary: Convert to/from timezone aware datetimes when storing in a DBMS
Home-page: https://github.com/nickw444/SQLAlchemy-UTCDateTime
Author: Nick Whyte
Author-email: nick@nickwhyte.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: SQLAlchemy-UTCDateTime
        ============================================
        
        Installation
        ++++++++++++
        
          pip install sqlalchemy-utcdatetime
        
        Sample Usage
        ++++++++++++
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
          import sqlalchemy as sa
          from sqlalchemy.ext.declarative import declarative_base
          from sqlalchemy_utcdatetime import UTCDateTime
          import datetime, pytz
        
          Base = declarative_base()
        
          class MyModel(Base):
              __tablename__ = 'my_model'
              
              id = sa.Column(sa.Integer(), primary_key=True)
              my_datetime = sa.Column(UTCDateTime())
        
        
          m = MyModel()
          m.my_datetime = datetime.datetime.now(pytz.timezone('Australia/Sydney'))
        
        
